cs.GT, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.DS, cs.SI 

This paper presents algorithms for computing Nash equilibria in structured game representations, which is a topic that falls under game theory (cs.GT) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The algorithms also exploit game structure through fast computation of the Jacobian of the payoff function, which involves techniques from optimization and numerical analysis (cs.DS). The paper also presents experimental results, which suggests that the algorithms may involve machine learning or statistical analysis (cs.LG) and may have practical applications in real-world scenarios (cs.SI).
